        "1429": {
          "vnum": 1429,
          "name": "Parched Field",
          "description": "Sage brush and bull thistle have claimed what was once a fine grazing pasture, before the rains stopped coming. To the northwest, the field descends to a riverbed, and to the south, field becomes prairie. You can't go that way. You can't go that way.",
